author: MSNBC.com
title: Lawrence: Dems have done great job outlining specifics of evidence against Trump
description: Lawrence O’Donnell says that Democrats “have done a great job … of outlining the specifics of the evidence and outlining the general principles.” Lawrence also brings up the challenges Democrats face during the impeachment trial on Saturday.
source.name: MSNBC

author: MSNBC.com
title: Chris Matthews: Trump setting precedent that presidents can get away with anything
description: Chris Matthews thinks that Trump has set a precedent on his abuse of power with Ukraine shortly after the Mueller Report’s release.
source.name: MSNBC

author: MSNBC.com
title: Chris Matthews: Trump’s crowd is running the govt, they’re a mob
description: Chris Matthews calls the figures surrounding Trump a mob: “This crowd is running the government, it’s unbelievable.”
source.name: MSNBC

author: MPX
title: Maya Wiley: Trump's actions like 'you bind the hands and feet...
description: On Trump's actions regarding obstruction of Congress, Maya Wiley says it's like "you bind the hands and feet of the Constitution."
source.name: MSNBC

title: Chris Matthews on message to GOP senators: 'Not only did [Trump] do this... he will keep doing it'

author: MSNBC.com
title: NPR: Mike Pompeo berated reporter after questions on Ukraine
description: NPR's Mary Louise Parker pushed Secy. of State Mike Pompeo repeatedly on Ukraine, and he reportedly berated her using curse words and demanding she find Ukraine on an unmarked map (which she did).
source.name: MSNBC

description: After reports emerged of the existence of an audio tape that appears to include Trump ordering aides to "get rid" of Amb. to Ukraine Marie Yovanovitch, ABC published the audio online.
source.name: MSNBC

author: MSNBC.com
title: Recording appears to show Trump interest in value of Ukraine aid
description: Joseph Bondy, attorney for Lev Parnas, joins Rachel Maddow and an MSNBC panel to discuss audio from 2018 that appears to show Donald Trump asking Parnas about how Ukraine would fare against Russia without U.S. aid.

title: Audio recording appears to show conversation between Parnas...

author: MSNBC.com
title: Day 1,100: House Dems close arguments with explicit call for Trump's removal
description: House managers finished up their opening arguments in their case against Trump, but it's unclear whether they'll be able to present any new evidence.

title: On third day of opening statements, new audio appears to confirm Trump’s role in Ukraine plot

author: MSNBC.com
title: Wiley: Trump's legal team 'did not have a lot to work with,' used what they had effectively
description: MSNBC legal analyst Maya Wiley talks about the defense strategy, and their advantage knowing where this jury already stood.
source.name: MSNBC

author: MSNBC.com
title: Schiff claims Trump's lawyers 'do not contest' the facts in the impeachment trial
description: Rep. Adam Schiff, D-Calif., said in a press conference that President Trump's lawyers "do not contest" the facts laid out in their case for impeachment.
source.name: MSNBC

author: MSNBC.com
title: Chris Murphy: Trump defense 'helped our case to win a vote on witnesses'
description: Following the opening statements by President Donald Trump's defense team, Senator Chris Murphy, D-CT., said that the lawyers 'peddled Russian propaganda' and helped make the case for witness testimony.

author: MSNBC.com
title: McCaskill: Argument by Trump's legal team is 'weak tea'
description: Fmr. Senator Claire McCaskill reacts to the opening arguments presented by President Donald Trump's legal team in his impeachment trial, which she says included "a Russian talking point without any factual backup."
source.name: MSNBC

author: MSNBC.com
title: Joy Reid: Democrats 'hate the president' is not a legal argument
description: Joy Reid breaks down the arguments presented by President Donald Trump's legal team prior to their opening argument in his impeachment trial.
source.name: MSNBC

author: MSNBC.com
title: Tim Kaine: GOP should treat Trump trial 'at least' as seriously as traffic court

author: MSNBC.com
title: Romney: 'I think it's very likely I'll be in favor of witnesses'

author: MSNBC.com
title: GOP senator: New audio tape 'not really relevant'

title: After days of fidget spinners, GOP senators ‘attentive’ during team Trump presentation

title: Williams: Can GOP really vote against witnesses because Schiff hurt their feelings?

title: 'False flag': Brian Williams, Sen. King call out Sekulow for saying Ukraine could have interfered with elections
description: MSNBC's Brian Williams and Sen. Angus King discuss defense attorney Jay Sekulow saying Ukraine, aside from Russia, could have interfered with the U.S. elections.
source.name: MSNBC

author: MSNBC.com
title: Schumer: Trump's defense team 'can't directly address the issues'
description: Sen. Chuck Schumer, D-N.Y., said he believed Trump's defense team "can't directly address the issues" during the impeachment trial in an interview with NBC News' Brian Williams.

title: Trump appears to show briefly on camera in Parnas recording

title: Full audio: Lev Parnas audio of alleged 2018 Trump conversation

title: Al Sharpton: Parnas tape 'very bad' for Trump
description: Rev. Al Sharpton notes that the recently released Lev Parnas tape shows that the president did know who Parnas was despite his previous statements. Sharpton says it’s “very bad for the president.”
